extractedData.name: Zenab Habib
extractedData.title: Software Engineer
extractedData.summary: Software Engineer with 2 years of experience in .NET full stack development, focusing on C#, .NET Core, MVC, SQL, and JavaScript. Skilled in building and maintaining web applications in Agile environments with Test-Driven Development. Experienced in software development, database design and code reviews. Strong problem-solving skills and a track record of contributing to collaborative, high-impact projects.

experience.description: Dedicated 2200+ hours to the State of Kentucky project, with a focus on building and maintaining full-stack applications using C#, .NET frameworks, JavaScript, SQL Server, Azure DevOps, and Angular, including development of a Health Insurance portal for the State of Kentucky.
achievements: Contributed 342 hours on integrating the Program of All-Inclusive Care for the Elderly into the Waiver application, with a 90% FTPR (first time pass rate), resulting in improved care outcomes and a 13% decrease in service costs.
Resolved over 60 bug fixes in 2024, and 28 fixes in 2025 so far, bringing a total of 118+ fixes during my tenure in this role, comprising of UI enhancements, code fixes and stored procedure changes.

Spearheaded improvements to the Provider Management Module by contributing 640 hours to a key Change Request, optimizing provider lookup/search functionality, providing ease of access to users and addressing 30+ bugs over 4 months.

certifications.name: Oracle Cloud Infrastructure (OCI) Certified Architect Associate
